data.name: One-Pot Turkey Chili
data.quickTastyDescription: A hearty and healthy turkey chili that's quick to make all in one pot!
detailedCookingInstructions: Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.
Add chopped onion and bell pepper, saut√© for 5 minutes until soft.
Add the ground turkey and cook until browned, about 5-7 minutes.
Stir in the chili powder, cumin, garlic powder, onion powder, and salt. Cook for another minute to toast the spices.
Add the diced tomatoes (with juices), kidney beans, black beans, and broth.
Bring to a simmer and cook for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Adjust seasoning if needed.
Serve hot, optionally topped with cheese or sour cream.
